<p>
{{~#line "0" "1"}}Give the king your justice, O God,{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}and your righteousness to the royal son!{{/line~}}
{{~#line "0" "2"}}May he judge your people with righteousness,{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}and your poor with justice!{{/line~}}
{{~#line "0" "3"}}Let the mountains bear prosperity for the people,{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}and the hills, in righteousness!{{/line~}}
{{~#line "0" "4"}}May he defend the cause of the poor of the people,{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}give deliverance to the children of the needy,{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}and crush the oppressor!{{/line~}}
</p><p>
{{~#line "0" "5"}}May they fear you while the sun endures,{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}and as long as the moon, throughout all generations!{{/line~}}
{{~#line "0" "6"}}May he be like rain that falls on the mown grass,{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}like showers that water the earth!{{/line~}}
{{~#line "0" "7"}}In his days may the righteous flourish,{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}and peace abound, till the moon be no more!{{/line~}}
</p><p>
{{~#line "0" "8"}}May he have dominion from sea to sea,{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}and from the River to the ends of the earth!{{/line~}}
{{~#line "0" "9"}}May desert tribes bow down before him,{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}and his enemies lick the dust!{{/line~}}
{{~#line "0" "10"}}May the kings of Tarshish and of the coastlands{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}render him tribute;{{/line~}}
{{~#line "0"}}may the kings of Sheba and Seba{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}bring gifts!{{/line~}}
{{~#line "0" "11"}}May all kings fall down before him,{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}all nations serve him!{{/line~}}
</p><p>
{{~#line "0" "12"}}For he delivers the needy when he calls,{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}the poor and him who has no helper.{{/line~}}
{{~#line "0" "13"}}He has pity on the weak and the needy,{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}and saves the lives of the needy.{{/line~}}
{{~#line "0" "14"}}From oppression and violence he redeems their life,{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}and precious is their blood in his sight.{{/line~}}
</p><p>
{{~#line "0" "15"}}Long may he live;{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}may gold of Sheba be given to him!{{/line~}}
{{~#line "0"}}May prayer be made for him continually,{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}and blessings invoked for him all the day!{{/line~}}
{{~#line "0" "16"}}May there be abundance of grain in the land;{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}on the tops of the mountains may it wave;{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}may its fruit be like Lebanon;{{/line~}}
{{~#line "0"}}and may people blossom in the cities{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}like the grass of the field!{{/line~}}
{{~#line "0" "17"}}May his name endure forever,{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}his fame continue as long as the sun!{{/line~}}
{{~#line "0"}}May people be blessed in him,{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}all nations call him blessed!{{/line~}}
</p><p>
{{~#line "0" "18"}}Blessed be the Lord, the God of Israel,{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}who alone does wondrous things.{{/line~}}
{{~#line "0" "19"}}Blessed be his glorious name forever;{{/line~}}
{{~#line "1"}}may the whole earth be filled with his glory!{{/line~}}
{{~#line "0"}}Amen and Amen!{{/line~}}
</p><p>
{{~#line "0" "20"}}The prayers of David, the son of Jesse, are ended.{{/line~}}
</p>
